CreateInstanceNew.document: This API is used to create clusters.
CreateInstanceNew.name: Creates clusters

DescribeClusterConfigs.document: This API is used to get the contents of the latest configuration files (config.xml, metrika.xml, and user.xml) of the cluster and display them to the user.
DescribeClusterConfigs.name: Gets the contents of the cluster configuration file

DescribeDatabaseAuditDownload.document: This API is used to download database audit logs.
DescribeDatabaseAuditDownload.name: Downloads database audit logs

DescribeDatabaseAuditRecords.document: This API is used to get database audit records.
DescribeDatabaseAuditRecords.name: Gets database audit records

DescribeInstance.document: This API is used to query the specific information of a cluster based on the cluster ID.
DescribeInstance.name: Accesses cluster description information

DescribeInstanceNodes.document: This API is used to get the list of cluster node information.
DescribeInstanceNodes.name: Gets the list of cluster node information

DescribeInstanceNodesInfo.document: This API is used to get the BE/FE node roles.
DescribeInstanceNodesInfo.name: Gets BE and FE node roles

DescribeInstanceState.document: This API is used to display cluster status, process progress, etc. in the cluster details page.
DescribeInstanceState.name: Gets cluster status

DescribeInstances.document: This API is used to get the list of clusters.
DescribeInstances.name: Gets the list of clusters

DescribeSlowQueryRecords.document: This API is used to get the slow log list.
DescribeSlowQueryRecords.name: Gets the slow log list

DescribeSlowQueryRecordsDownload.document: This API is used to download slow log files.
DescribeSlowQueryRecordsDownload.name: Downloads slow log files

DestroyInstance.document: This API is used to terminate clusters.
DestroyInstance.name: Terminates clusters

ModifyInstance.document: This API is used to modify the cluster's name.
ModifyInstance.name: Modifies the cluster's name

ResizeDisk.document: This API is used to expand cloud disks.
ResizeDisk.name: Expands cloud disks

RestartClusterForNode.document: This API is used to indicate the rolling restart of the clusters.
RestartClusterForNode.name: Rolling restart of the cluster

ScaleOutInstance.document: This API is used to horizontally scale out nodes.
ScaleOutInstance.name: Scales out horizontally

ScaleUpInstance.document: This API is used to scale up/down computing resources.
ScaleUpInstance.name: Scales up/down computing resources
